    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward.</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Geofroy</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 6, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your communication of the 28th ultimo relative to certain duties exacted of
                    Messrs. Brulaton &amp; Co., of New Orleans, and, in reply, to inform you that I
                    have transmitted a translation thereof to the Secretary of the Treasury, who has
                    been requested to investigate the matter, with a view to the adoption of such
                    proceedings as the result may call for.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">L. de Geofroy,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
